<br>
In my book this is pure symbolism.  I am not sure if people realize that the biggest losers from their boycotts are often the folks in their own country who work to distribute/produce the product in question.  The following article in MSNBC gave me a good laugh about certain folks in Hamburg, Germany and elsewhere trying to start a boycott of American goods.  While this article focuses on a boycott taking place in Europe, I think the same arguments hold true for a boycott taking place in the United States.<br>
